{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, Sniffles2 infers positional connections that help resolve a given complex allele architecture with information that aCGH alone cannot provide.",
    "We know from many studies that germline variants are not the only source of structural variation.",
    "Often, somatic/mosaic variants are important.",
    "This has been indicated in, for example, cancer and neurological disorders 9, 12.",
    "Thus, Sniffles2 is equipped with a mosaic mode to identify low-frequency (5-20% variant allele frequency (VAF)) SVs"
  ]
}